<div id="p619299" class="blockpost rowodd">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#7</span> <a href="viewtopic.php?pid=619299#p619299">2009-09-14 18:17:21</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postbody">
				<div class="postleft">
					<dl>
						<dt><strong>thayer</strong></dt>
						<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Fellow</strong></dd>
						<dd class="postavatar"><img src="https://bbs.archlinux.org/img/avatars/11008.png?m=1281192708" width="24" height="19" alt="" /></dd>
						<dd><span>From: Vancouver, BC</span></dd>
						<dd><span>Registered: 2007-05-20</span></dd>
						<dd><span>Posts: 1,560</span></dd>
						<dd class="usercontacts"><span class="website"><a href="http://cinderwick.ca" rel="nofollow">Website</a></span></dd>
					</dl>
				</div>
				<div class="postright">
					<h3>Re: Dmenu Hacking Thread</h3>
					<div class="postmsg">
						<p>I picked this up somewhere in the wild...a netcfg profile selector:</p><div class="codebox"><pre><code>#!/bin/sh

nf=&#039;#888888&#039;
nb=&#039;#2a2a2a&#039;
sf=&#039;#ffffff&#039;
sb=&#039;#2a2a2a&#039;
font=&#039;-*-terminus-medium-r-*-*-12-*-*-*-*-*-*-*&#039;
dmenucmd=&quot;dmenu -fn $font -nb $nb -nf $nf -sb $sb -sf $sf&quot;

netprof=`ls -1 /etc/network.d | $dmenucmd $*` 
if [ &quot;x$netprof&quot; != &quot;x&quot; ]; then
    /usr/bin/sudo /usr/bin/netcfg2 -a
    /usr/bin/sudo /usr/bin/netcfg2 $netprof
fi</code></pre></div>
					</div>
					<div class="postsignature postmsg"><hr /><p><strong>thayer williams</strong> ~ <a href="http://cinderwick.ca/" rel="nofollow">cinderwick.ca</a></p></div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
